Implements:
	./hello 70 <- Will use the default cube.off, scaled by 70

	./hello 70 Whatever.off <- Will load the specified model, scaled by 70.

However, if no command line arguments are given the program will prompt the user as follows

This document describes how to operate Lab1 if no arguments are given

Step 1:
	Enter a numerical value into the terminal corresponding to the model that is to be displayed.
	Option 5 allows the user to enter there own OFF file location to be displayed.

Step 2:
	Program key command include the following:
	"q": To quit the program.
	"s": To save the framebuffer to a file called "image.ppm".

